, 11. in conventu Uticensi. ‘Conventus' is the Latin equivalent oi διοίκησις, the term applied to the ‘politieal districts’ or ‘jurisdictione' into which certain Roman provinces were divided: see Pliu. H. N. v. 29, where ‘conventus' is used synonymously with ‘iurisdictio' Cicero pro naq. 8 ‘conventus firmi atque magni [erant in Africa].'
